[2
Date: Thu, 19 Aug 1999 12:32:43 -0400
From: Barbara Hatch Rosenberg <bhrosenb@purvid.purchase.edu>

The use of riot control agents in warfare is banned. Riot control agents
are defined in the CWC as chemicals not listed in the treaty, "which can
produce rapidly in humans sensory irritation or disabling physical
effects which disappear within a short time following termination of
exposure."
It sounds like the symptoms in the Sudan are not disappearing within a
short time. In that case the use of a chemical to cause the observed
symptoms for hostile purposes is prohibited by the CWC.
--
